<h2 id="who-its-for">👥 Who Is Gorgias For?</h2>

**Ideal operators:**
- Shopify or BigCommerce stores processing 500+ support tickets monthly
- Brands with $2M+ annual revenue where support quality directly impacts retention
- Subscription businesses using Recharge where support drives churn reduction
- Teams ready to invest in automation setup to realize long-term savings
- Operators who need revenue attribution to justify support investment

**Skip Gorgias if:**
- You're processing under 300 tickets monthly — the ROI doesn't materialize
- Your business isn't ecommerce-focused — generic helpdesks serve you better
- You're on a tight budget and can't absorb per-ticket overages
- Your primary platform isn't Shopify — integrations are weaker elsewhere
- You need enterprise phone center features — look at Gladly or Kustomer

For multi-location service businesses rather than ecommerce, our <a href="/reviews/help-scout-review">Help Scout review</a> covers a better-suited alternative.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Tip:</strong> Run the numbers before committing. Export your current ticket data, project 12 months, and calculate Gorgias costs versus per-agent alternatives. The break-even point depends entirely on your automation success rate.
</div>

<h2 id="implementation">🚀 Implementation Reality</h2>

Gorgias advertises quick setup, and for basic configuration, that's accurate. Our team got a Shopify store receiving emails through Gorgias in 22 minutes.

However, meaningful implementation takes 2-4 weeks:

**Week 1:** Channel connections, basic macros, team onboarding. Expect 20% productivity loss as agents learn the interface.

**Week 2:** Automation rules buildout, AI Agent training data collection, self-service portal content.

**Week 3-4:** Optimization — refining rules, A/B testing macros, tuning AI responses based on escalation patterns.

The biggest mistake we see: operators going live with minimal configuration, experiencing poor results, and blaming the tool. Gorgias rewards investment in setup. Allocate a dedicated resource for the first month.

<h2 id="alternatives">🔄 Gorgias Alternatives</h2>

**Zendesk:** Better for hybrid businesses with both ecommerce and non-ecommerce support needs. Per-agent pricing scales more predictably. Weaker ecommerce integrations.

**Freshdesk:** Budget-friendly with solid automation. Ecommerce integrations require third-party apps. Good choice under 1,000 monthly tickets.

**Kustomer:** Enterprise alternative with better phone integration. Higher price point but includes AI features. Consider above $10M annual revenue.

**Richpanel:** Newer competitor with similar ecommerce focus. Self-service portal is strong. Less mature automation engine.

**Gladly:** Radically different approach — organizes around customers rather than tickets. Premium pricing, premium experience. For brands where support is a differentiator.

<h2 id="final-verdict">🏆 Final Verdict</h2>

Gorgias earns its position as the default helpdesk for serious ecommerce operators in 2026. The Shopify integration depth, AI Agent capabilities, and revenue attribution create genuine operational advantages that generic helpdesks can't match.

The per-ticket pricing model remains controversial. For high-volume operators, costs can exceed alternatives significantly. But when automation works — and our team achieved 40-60% deflection rates consistently — the effective cost per inquiry drops below traditional helpdesks while delivering better customer experience.

**Our recommendation:** If you're running a Shopify store above $2M annually with 500+ monthly support tickets, Gorgias should be your default choice. The productivity gains, revenue attribution, and customer context justify the investment. Commit to proper implementation, build your automation incrementally, and negotiate pricing on annual contracts.

For smaller operations or non-ecommerce businesses, explore Freshdesk or Help Scout first. The Gorgias ROI requires ticket volume to amortize the automation setup investment.

